                "url": "/topics/other"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499409",
        "quote": "Remember that stress doesn't come from what's going on in your life. It comes from your thoughts about what's going on in your life.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499409"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Thoughts",
                "url": "/topics/thoughts"
            },
            {
                "name": "Remember",
                "url": "/topics/remember"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499434",
        "quote": "The number of stressors has multiplied exponentially: traffic, money, success, work/life balance, the economy, the environment, parenting, family conflict, relationships, disease. As the nature of human life has become far more complicated, our ancient stress response hasn't been able to keep up.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499434"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Life",
                "url": "/topics/life"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Our",
                "url": "/topics/our"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499428",
        "quote": "Negative thoughts stick around because we believe them, not because we want them or choose them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499428"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Thoughts",
                "url": "/topics/thoughts"
            },
            {
                "name": "Negative",
                "url": "/topics/negative"
            },
            {
                "name": "Want",
                "url": "/topics/want"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499412",
        "quote": "Stress is the negative whirlwind of emotions that gets imposed on top of our stimulation and engagement.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499412"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Negative",
                "url": "/topics/negative"
            },
            {
                "name": "Whirlwind",
                "url": "/topics/whirlwind"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499407",
        "quote": "We need to distinguish between stress and stimulation. Having deadlines, setting goals, and pushing yourself to perform at capacity are stimulating. Stress is when you're anxious, upset, or frustrated, which dramatically reduce your ability to perform.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499407"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Upset",
                "url": "/topics/upset"
            },
            {
                "name": "Your",
                "url": "/topics/your"
            },
            {
                "name": "Frustrated",
                "url": "/topics/frustrated"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499432",
        "quote": "During the financial crisis, I worked with hundreds of executives who struggled as a result of their thoughts about job security. When their beliefs changed, so did their emotional experience - and they were then able to focus on the task at hand more effectively.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499432"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Financial Crisis",
                "url": "/topics/financial_crisis"
            },
            {
                "name": "About",
                "url": "/topics/about"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499415",
        "quote": "The more you worry, the more you throw off the delicate balance of hormones required for health.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499415"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Balance",
                "url": "/topics/balance"
            },
            {
                "name": "Worry",
                "url": "/topics/worry"
            },
            {
                "name": "Delicate",
                "url": "/topics/delicate"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499413",
        "quote": "If you're successful and stressed out, you're succeeding in spite of your stress, not because of it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499413"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Stressed",
                "url": "/topics/stressed"
            },
            {
                "name": "Spite",
                "url": "/topics/spite"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499430",
        "quote": "Stress is never a given. There are people who get divorced amicably. There are people who pack up and move with no emotional toll. There is no stressor 'out there' in the world. We experience stress - or we don't - depending on what we believe.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499430"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Move",
                "url": "/topics/move"
            },
            {
                "name": "Given",
                "url": "/topics/given"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499408",
        "quote": "Some people are so used to experiencing stress that they don't remember what life was like without it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499408"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Like",
                "url": "/topics/like"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499416",
        "quote": "Worrisome thoughts and their resulting feelings are a form of self strangulation. They not only strangle your emotions. They affect your physical life as well, and your ability to focus and get things done.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499416"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Thoughts",
                "url": "/topics/thoughts"
            },
            {
                "name": "Emotions",
                "url": "/topics/emotions"
            },
            {
                "name": "Affect",
                "url": "/topics/affect"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499410",
        "quote": "Stress is a byproduct of subconscious beliefs you have about the world. You can't choose not to believe something. You believe it because you think it's true. To eliminate stress, you must learn to challenge these beliefs so that you see them differently.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499410"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Learn",
                "url": "/topics/learn"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499420",
        "quote": "The elusive truth is that there is nothing stress-producing in the physical world. Things simply are. Molecules move. Light and sound appear.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499420"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Nothing",
                "url": "/topics/nothing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Move",
                "url": "/topics/move"
            },
            {
                "name": "Molecules",
                "url": "/topics/molecules"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499427",
        "quote": "Look closer at the stress in your own life and you can identify that negative emotions are always built on counterfactual statements.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499427"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Emotions",
                "url": "/topics/emotions"
            },
            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499421",
        "quote": "What's taking place during stress is actually much simpler than a transaction between stressful life events and you. There aren't two parties involved in stress. There is only one - your own mind.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499421"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Mind",
                "url": "/topics/mind"
            },
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499422",
        "quote": "To believe that your husband, wife, parents, kids, boss, job, bank account, or body is even partly responsible for your emotions, to think that there are bullets 'out there' that you have to contend with, that there are stressful life events to overcome, is to miss something vital.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499422"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Boss",
                "url": "/topics/boss"
            },
            {
                "name": "Husband",
                "url": "/topics/husband"
            },
            {
                "name": "Overcome",
                "url": "/topics/overcome"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499411",
        "quote": "People often say that stress is a motivator. What we're referring to when we say this is really better described as stimulation and engagement.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499411"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Engagement",
                "url": "/topics/engagement"
            },
            {
                "name": "Often",
                "url": "/topics/often"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499414",
        "quote": "We all enjoy pushing ourselves to accomplish our objectives. But we don't need stress to get there.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499414"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Stress",
                "url": "/topics/stress"
            },
            {
                "name": "Accomplish",
                "url": "/topics/accomplish"
            },
            {
                "name": "Need",
                "url": "/topics/need"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499417",
        "quote": "When a friend is sick, I see the situation for what it is, not what it isn't, and I offer to help as much as she wants, not as much as I want.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499417"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Want",
                "url": "/topics/want"
            },
            {
                "name": "Sick",
                "url": "/topics/sick"
            },
            {
                "name": "I See",
                "url": "/topics/i_see"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499418",
        "quote": "Find the beliefs that are strangling your feelings, challenge them for your sake as well as theirs, and see how it feels to love someone without a thought about the future, simply for who they are today.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Andrew J. Bernstein",
            "url": "/quotes/andrew_j_bernstein_499418"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Love",
                "url": "/topics/love"
